:"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Murray","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Moray in northeastern Scotland, which derives from Celtic <i>mori-</i> ‘sea’ + <i>treb-</i> ‘settlement’. The founder of the Scottish house of Murray was a Fleming named Freskin who was granted Strathbrock in West Lothian and Duffus in Moray by David I. The family took its name from the region in the late 12th century.","Irish and Scottish: shortened form of   McMurray  .","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Muireadhaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Muireadhach</i>’ a personal name meaning ‘mariner’. Occasionally it may be a shortened form of   McMurray  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Murri","meanings":["Probably Scottish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murry","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murrah","meanings":["Probably an altered form of Scottish   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murie","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Michel.","Scottish: habitational name from Murie in Errol (Perthshire).","Scottish and Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Merhi","meanings":["Arabic (mainly Lebanon and Syria): from a variant of the personal name <i>Mirhi</i> of unknown meaning. Bearers of this surname are both Muslims and Christians. Compare   Murray   5."]},{"name":"Murrey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"McMurray","meanings":["Irish (northern) and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Muireadhaigh</b> or <b>Mac Muireadhaich</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Muireadhach</i> ‘seafarer’ (see   Murdoch  ). Compare   McCurry   1."]},{"name":"Murra","meanings":["Italian (Sicily): topographic name from Sicilian <i>murra</i> ‘large rock, mass of rocks’ or a habitational name from a place called with this word.","East Frisian: unexplained.","Albanian: nickname from <i>murrë</i> (definite form <i>murra</i>) ‘dark gray cow’."]},{"name":"Murrie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Murray  ."]}]},{"name":"Sir","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Simon  , now rare, but more common in the Middle Ages, when it gave rise to the surnames <i>Simms</i> and <i>Simpson</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Simon","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]},{"name":"Andrew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the Greek name <i>Andreas</i>, a short form of any of various compound names derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Andrew Murray 2nd Laird of Tullibardine was born in 1284, in Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom as the son of William Murray Ist of Tullibardine. He had at least 1 son with Lady Christian Bruce aka \"de Bruce, de Seton, de Moray\". He died on 5 October 1332, in his hometown, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1284–5 Oct 1332":"1284–5. oktoober 1332","1260–1332":"1260–1332","1274–1335":"1274–1335","1274–Female":"1274–Surnud","1279–Male":"1279–Surnud","1284–1332":"1284–1332","1310–1333":"1310–1333","1273–1356":"1273–1356","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1255–1297":"1255–1297","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1297":"1297","1352":"1352","1274":"1274","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Aft 24 May 1297":"pärast 24. maid 1297","1335":"1335","1356":"1356","1279":"1279","1333":"1333","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","5 Oct 1332":"5. oktoober 1332","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1284–5 Oct 1332":"1284–5. lokakuuta 1332","1260–1332":"1260–1332","1274–1335":"1274–1335","1274–Female":"1274–Kuollut","1279–Male":"1279–Kuollut","1284–1332":"1284–1332","1310–1333":"1310–1333","1273–1356":"1273–1356","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1255–1297":"1255–1297","about 1290":"noin 1290","1297":"1297","1352":"1352","1274":"1274","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Aft 24 May 1297":"24. toukokuuta 1297 jälkeen","1335":"1335","1356":"1356","1279":"1279","1333":"1333","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","5 Oct 1332":"5. lokakuuta 1332","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1284–5 Oct 1332":"1284–5 octobre 1332","1260–1332":"1260–1332","1274–1335":"1274–1335","1274–Female":"1274–Décédée","1279–Male":"1279–Décédé","1284–1332":"1284–1332","1310–1333":"1310–1333","1273–1356":"1273–1356","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1255–1297":"1255–1297","about 1290":"environ 1290","1297":"1297","1352":"1352","1274":"1274","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","12